row.description:
Now, some questions about your alcohol consumption. When we use the word 'drink' it means: 

  • One bottle or can of beer or a glass of draft
  • One glass of wine or a wine cooler
  • One drink or cocktail with 1 and a 1/2 onces of liquor
The next questions are about the foods you usually eat or drink. Think about all the foods you eat, both meals and snacks, at home and away from home.
This section is about physical activity. We are intersted only in physical activities not related to work, that is, leisure time activities.

Lastly, this section is about certain chronic conditions which you may have. We are interested in "long term conditions" which are expected to last or have already lasted 6 months or more and that have been diagnosed by a health professional.
